---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE, LEGAL } from '../consts';
---
<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How MoveWell Reviews collects, uses, and protects your information.">
  <p class="notice">
    This policy is a thorough starting template, not legal advice. Replace the
    <code>[placeholders]</code> in <code>src/consts.js</code> with your real business details, and
    have a qualified attorney review it before launch — especially once you add specific analytics,
    ad networks, or email tools, each of which has its own required disclosures.
  </p>

  <p class="lead">
    {LEGAL.entity} ("we," "us," or "our") operates {SITE.name} ({SITE.domain}). This Privacy Policy
    explains what information we collect when you visit the site, how we use it, and the choices you have.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Usage &amp; analytics data:</strong> pages visited, referring site, device and browser type, and approximate location derived from your IP address, collected through privacy-respecting analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Newsletter sign-ups:</strong> your email address, if you voluntarily subscribe. Submissions are processed by our form provider (Formspree) and email tool.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact form submissions:</strong> your name, email, subject, and message, if you contact us.</li>
    <li><strong>Affiliate click data:</strong> which outbound affiliate links were clicked and from which page, in aggregate, so we understand which content is useful. We do not tie this to information that identifies you personally.</li>
    <li><strong>Cookies &amp; local storage:</strong> a small record of your cookie-consent choice, and any cookies set by analytics you have accepted.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not knowingly collect payment card numbers, passwords, Social Security numbers, or government IDs — we never ask for them on this site.</p>

  <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To operate, maintain, and improve the site and understand which content is helpful.</li>
    <li>To send newsletter emails, only if you opted in, and to let you unsubscribe at any time.</li>
    <li>To respond to messages you send through our contact form or by email.</li>
    <li>To measure, in aggregate, which reviews and affiliate links perform well.</li>
    <li>To detect, prevent, and address security issues, fraud, or abuse.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Cookies and tracking</h2>
  <p>
    We use minimal cookies and local storage. Essential storage remembers your consent choice.
    Any analytics or advertising cookies load only after you accept them via our consent banner.
    You can control or delete cookies through your browser settings at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>4. How we share information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information for money. We share information only as follows:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Service providers</strong> who process data on our behalf — website hosting (Hostinger), form handling and email delivery (Formspree and our email provider), and analytics. These providers may only use the data to perform services for us.</li>
    <li><strong>Affiliate networks and retailers</strong> (such as the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program, ShareASale, Impact, and CJ Affiliate). When you click an affiliate link and leave our site, the destination site's own privacy policy governs — see our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal reasons</strong> — if required by law, subpoena, or to protect rights, safety, and property.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Your California privacy rights (CCPA / CPRA)</h2>
  <p>
    If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we collect,
    to request access to or deletion of your personal information, to correct inaccurate information,
    and to opt out of the "sale" or "sharing" of personal information for cross-context behavioral
    advertising. We do not sell your personal information for money.
    {LEGAL.sharesDataForAds
      ? ' Because we use advertising partners that may "share" data for interest-based ads, you can exercise your opt-out via our '
      : ' If we ever use advertising partners that share data for interest-based ads, we will honor opt-outs via our '}
    <a href="/do-not-sell">Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information</a> page. We will not
    discriminate against you for exercising any of these rights. To make a request, see
    <a href="/do-not-sell">Do Not Sell or Share</a> or email
    <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL.privacyEmail}`}>{LEGAL.privacyEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Other US state privacy rights</h2>
  <p>
    Residents of states with comprehensive privacy laws (including Virginia, Colorado, Connecticut,
    Utah, Texas, and others) may have similar rights to access, correct, delete, and opt out of
    targeted advertising or profiling. Contact us at
    <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL.privacyEmail}`}>{LEGAL.privacyEmail}</a> to exercise these rights.
  </p>

  <h2>7. EU / UK visitors (GDPR)</h2>
  <p>
    If you are in the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, you may have rights of access,
    rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and objection under the GDPR/UK GDPR. Our legal
    bases for processing are your consent (for the newsletter and non-essential cookies) and our
    legitimate interests (in operating and securing the site). Contact us to exercise these rights.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This site is intended for adults and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly
    collect personal information from children under 13, consistent with the Children's Online Privacy
    Protection Act (COPPA). If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will
    delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Data retention &amp; security</h2>
  <p>
    We retain newsletter and contact data only as long as needed for the purposes described above, or
    as required by law. We use reasonable technical and organizational safeguards to protect your
    information, but no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date above reflects the most
    recent revision. Material changes will be highlighted on this page.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy or a data request? Email
    <a href={`mailto:${LEGAL.privacyEmail}`}>{LEGAL.privacyEmail}</a> or write to us at:
  </p>
  <p>
    {LEGAL.entity}<br />
    {LEGAL.addressLine1}<br />
    {LEGAL.addressLine2}
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
